The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks, specifically named entity recognition, in electronic health records (EHRs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related tasks. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning), and the use of transfer learning, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with data privacy concerns, which suggests the category cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper mentions the use of embeddings, which suggests the category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
